section.section:
The Program shall be open to any individual who:
Is a resident of the State;
Is a Medicare beneficiary;
Is not enrolled in a Medicare Advantage Plan or other public or private insurance program, except for Medicaid and the Maryland Pharmacy Assistance Program, that provides prescription drug benefits at the time that the individual applies for enrollment in the Program;
Has an annual household income below 150 percent of the federal poverty level; and
Meets the asset test established by the Medicare Modernization Act under Medicare Part D.

text.section:
The Department may:
Enter into a contract with one or more prescription drug plans to coordinate the prescription drug benefits provided under the Program and the Medicare Part D prescription drug benefit;
Require a pharmaceutical manufacturer to provide rebates in an amount not less than the rebates provided to the Medicaid Program under § 1927(c) of Title XIX of the Social Security Act (42 U.S.C. § 1396r-8) as a condition of the pharmaceutical manufacturer's products being available to enrollees;
Enroll eligible individuals into a prescription drug plan under contract with the Department, with an opt-out provision at the individual's discretion;
Specify procedures for individuals to apply for enrollment in the Program;
Contract with a private entity to assist in administration of the Program or negotiations with prescription drug plans; and
Pay all or part of the premiums, deductibles, coinsurance payments, and copayments required under the Medicare Part D Program for enrollees.
